When an action affects multiple parts of the page (e.g., deleting a todo updates the list AND a count badge), we use the `HX-Trigger` response header to fire events that other elements listen for. This keeps components decoupled while still allowing coordination.

The scaffolding is solid. These patterns will shape every endpoint we build. Let me know your thoughts -- particularly on how you want to structure the Askama templates for fragment vs full-page rendering.

